# Freshsales Review: The AI-Powered CRM Built for Small Teams

[Freshsales](https://www.freshworks.com/crm/sales/) is a cloud-based, AI-powered CRM designed to help small and mid-sized sales teams streamline deals, score leads, and close faster. It stands out in a crowded market by bundling affordable pricing with intelligent automation powered by Freddy AI, a built-in virtual sales assistant that learns from your team's win patterns. The result: teams spend less time on admin and more time selling.

## What Is Freshsales?

[Freshsales](https://www.freshworks.com/crm/sales/) is a sales CRM that simplifies deal tracking, lead management, and team collaboration in one visual pipeline. Unlike many competitors that charge extra for AI features or force you to buy a dialer separately, Freshsales bundles its intelligent lead scoring engine (Freddy AI) and built-in phone system across all paid tiers. You can manage contacts, run sales sequences, log calls and emails, track deals in a kanban view, and receive next-best-action recommendations without juggling third-party tools.

It's especially built for sales teams at companies with 5 to 200 employees that want a practical, no-nonsense alternative to enterprise systems like Salesforce or HubSpot, where feature bloat and pricing can quickly spiral.

## Who Freshsales Is For

**Freshsales fits best if you:**

- Run a lean sales team (5 to 50 reps) that needs to hit quota without complex integrations or months of implementation
- Want AI-powered lead scoring without paying HubSpot prices
- Prefer a cleaner UI over feature maximalism
- Need a phone system built into your CRM, not bolted on
- Are frustrated with your current CRM's reporting or support but don't want to overhaul your entire sales stack

**Freshsales is NOT the right choice if you:**

- Require enterprise-grade custom reporting and predictive pipeline analytics
- Need deep integrations across 50+ tools
- Have complex multi-currency, multi-language compliance requirements
- Depend on 24/7 priority support (some users report slow ticket resolution)
- Want a mobile-first experience for field sales teams

## Key Features

### Freddy AI: The Standout

[Freddy AI](https://www.freshworks.com/crm/freddy-ai/) is Freshsales' brain. It analyzes engagement signals (email opens, link clicks, call duration, meeting notes) against your team's historical win data and automatically flags hot leads as "Likely to Buy." It also groups deals into health buckets (At Risk, Trending, Likely to Close, Gone Cold) and suggests the next best action for each deal.

Freddy is available on Pro and Enterprise plans. The Growth plan lacks lead scoring, which is a significant limitation if AI-powered prioritization is why you're considering Freshsales.

### Built-In Phone System

Unlike many CRMs that charge $50-$100 per month for a dedicated dialer, Freshsales includes a cloud phone across all paid plans. You can make and receive calls directly from the contact record, and Freshsales automatically logs the call duration, notes, and outcome. It's not as feature-rich as Close's Power Dialer or RingCentral, but for teams making 20-30 calls per day, it's more than adequate.

### Sales Sequences and Email Automation

Create automated multi-step outreach campaigns that trigger based on contact behavior or timers. You can automate email sends, task assignments, and deal stage changes. Two-way email sync means all incoming messages automatically log to the contact record, eliminating manual data entry.

### Kanban Pipeline and Contact Management

Visualize your entire pipeline at a glance with drag-and-drop deal cards. Customize fields, add custom stages, and filter by owner, pipeline, or team. Contacts are auto-enriched with industry, company size, and other firmographic data, giving you context before you dial.

### Native Integrations

Freshsales integrates with Gmail, Outlook, Zoom, Microsoft Teams, Google Calendar, Slack, and Zapier. However, compared to HubSpot or Zoho CRM, the integration marketplace is smaller, so you may hit a wall if you rely on niche tools.

## Freshsales Pricing Breakdown

### Plans and Per-User Costs

All pricing is per user, per month, billed annually. Monthly billing costs 20-30% more.

- **Free Plan**: $0/month. Up to 3 users. Basic contact and deal management. No custom fields, no workflows, no reports, no Freddy AI, no phone. Best for testing only.
- **Growth Plan**: $15/user/month (annual billing). Up to 10 custom fields, basic workflows, sales sequences, built-in phone, email tracking. No Freddy AI lead scoring.
- **Pro Plan**: $39/user/month (annual billing). Full Freddy AI lead scoring and deal insights, custom reports, advanced automations, SMS and live chat, up to 50 custom fields.
- **Enterprise Plan**: $69/user/month (annual billing). Everything in Pro plus priority support, advanced permissions, SSO, and dedicated account management.

### Hidden Costs to Watch

Freshsales includes storage of contacts, deals, and notes within the plan. However, premium integrations (like syncing with certain marketing automation platforms) may cost extra. If you need advanced reporting or data migration during onboarding, support incidents can be slow to resolve, which adds to your time cost.

For a 10-person team on the Pro plan, you're looking at $390 per month or $4,680 per year. At that scale, Freshsales is 40-50% cheaper than HubSpot Sales Hub ($50/user/month) and comparable to Pipedrive.

## Strengths of Freshsales

**1. Unbeatable Price-to-Value Ratio**
For pure CRM functionality with a phone and AI built in, Freshsales offers arguably the best bang for your buck. Most competitors either charge more, offer less, or lock advanced features behind higher tiers.

**2. Fast Onboarding**
Users consistently report going from signup to first pipeline setup in under an hour. The UI is intuitive enough that reps adopt it without extensive training. Comparison to HubSpot and Salesforce, which require weeks of configuration, is striking.

**3. Freddy AI Actually Works**
Unlike some AI features that feel gimmicky, Freddy's lead scoring and deal health predictions are genuinely useful. Teams report better focus on high-intent deals and fewer lost leads falling through the cracks.

**4. Built-In Phone Saves Money**
Every paid plan includes a phone system. You avoid the extra $50-$100 per user per month that other CRMs charge for a dialer.

**5. Clean, Non-Overwhelming UI**
Freshsales resists feature bloat. The interface is modern, the dashboard is readable, and reps actually log activities because the friction is low. This is a major advantage over Zoho CRM, which many users describe as cluttered.

## Weaknesses of Freshsales

**1. Reporting Is Basic**
The custom report builder is limited compared to HubSpot or Salesforce. If your sales leader needs multi-touch attribution, win/loss analysis, or advanced pipeline forecasting, Freshsales will frustrate you. Email metrics (open and click rates) are very basic.

**2. Limited Integration Ecosystem**
Compared to HubSpot or Zoho CRM, Freshsales has fewer pre-built integrations. If your martech stack includes niche tools, you may have to build Zapier workarounds, which add fragility and require ongoing maintenance.

**3. Customer Support Is Inconsistent**
Multiple reviewers report slow ticket resolution times, especially for integration or data migration issues. Premium support is only available on the Enterprise plan. For a mid-market team, this can become a pain point.

**4. Mobile App Is Bare Bones**
The mobile app covers basics like contact lookup, call logging, and deal updates, but it lacks the polish and features of HubSpot or Pipedrive. Field sales teams may feel hamstrung.

**5. Freddy AI Only on Higher Tiers**
Lead scoring is locked behind the Pro plan at $39/user/month. The Growth plan at $15/user/month gets sequences and email but no AI, which undercuts Freshsales' main differentiator for budget-conscious buyers.

**6. Some Users Report Recurring Bugs**
A minority of reviewers mention system stability issues and recurring bugs that require extended support interactions. This is not widespread, but it's worth noting if you have mission-critical deal flow.

## Freshsales vs. the Competition

### Freshsales vs. HubSpot CRM

[HubSpot CRM](https://www.hubspot.com/) has a free plan with unlimited users and basic automation. HubSpot's ecosystem is deeper (you can add Sales Hub, Marketing Hub, Service Hub), making it ideal for companies that want one platform across revenue ops. HubSpot's reporting and AI are more sophisticated, but you pay for it. Sales Hub starts at $50/user/month, more than Freshsales Pro.

**Winner:** If you need a CRM-only tool and budget matters, Freshsales. If you want an all-in-one platform and have budget, HubSpot.

### Freshsales vs. Pipedrive

[Pipedrive](https://www.pipedrive.com/) is also pipeline-first and affordable, starting at $14.90/user/month. Pipedrive's interface is slightly more intuitive (deal animations and visual cues), but it lacks Freshsales' built-in phone and AI lead scoring. Pipedrive wins on user experience for deal tracking; Freshsales wins on automation and AI.

**Winner:** If you want the most intuitive pipeline, Pipedrive. If you want AI and a phone included, Freshsales.

### Freshsales vs. Zoho CRM

[Zoho CRM](https://www.zoho.com/crm/) is highly customizable and integrates deeply within the Zoho ecosystem (Zoho Mail, Zoho Books, Zoho Cliq). Zoho's free plan is generous, and pricing is comparable to Freshsales. However, Zoho's UI is busier, and its AI features (Zia) are less intuitive. Freshsales' lead scoring is more straightforward.

**Winner:** If you live in the Zoho ecosystem, Zoho CRM. If you want simplicity and better AI, Freshsales.

### Freshsales vs. Salesforce Essentials

[Salesforce Essentials](https://www.salesforce.com/products/essentials/) is stripped-down Salesforce at $165/user/month for three users, or $55/user/month. It's enterprise-grade but overkill and expensive for small teams. Freshsales is better for lean sales teams.

**Winner:** Freshsales, unless you need Salesforce's brand or are already in the Salesforce ecosystem.

### Freshsales vs. Monday Sales CRM

[Monday Sales CRM](https://monday.com/crm/) is workflow-first and visual, with flexible automation. However, it lacks a built-in phone and advanced AI. Freshsales is more specialized for sales; Monday CRM is better if you need cross-team project visibility.

**Winner:** Freshsales for pure sales. Monday CRM for hybrid sales and project teams.

